[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ryan Broom: Bristol Rovers midfielder extends contract at League One club

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bristol Rovers midfielder Ryan Broom has signed an extended contract with the League One club.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 20-year-old has made seven senior appearances for Rovers so far in his career.
Born in Wales, he has previously had loan spells at non-league sides Taunton Town and Bath City.
One of five players offered a new deal by boss Darrell Clarke at the end of the season, Broom is the second to sign on so far, after defender James Clarke.
